text: Ulamambri is a village in north-western New South Wales, Australia. ==Geography== Ulamambri is on the junction of the Castlereagh River and Ulamambri Creek, just south of the town of Coonabarabran, New South Wales. Ulamambri is in Toorawandi parish of Napier County, New South Wales.Map of Napier County The parish is on the traditional lands of the Weilwan Aboriginal people. ==Railway== A railway station on the now closed Gwabegar railway line was located there between 1917 and 1976.Ulamambri,station NSWrail.net, accessed 9 April 2010. The suburb of Ulamambri, adjoins Coonabarabran to the north west. ==References== Category:Localities in New South Wales Category:Warrumbungle Shire Category:Central West (New South Wales)
